## Implementation Details

### Page: `apps/dashboard/src/app/projects/[id]/deployments/page.tsx`

The deployments list page. Shows all deployments for the project with pagination and optional type filtering.

#### Data Fetching

```typescript
"use client";

import { useParams, useSearchParams, useRouter } from "next/navigation";
import useSWR from "swr";
import { fetcher } from "@/lib/swr";

export default function DeploymentsPage() {
  const params = useParams();
  const searchParams = useSearchParams();
  const projectId = params.id as string;

  const page = parseInt(searchParams.get("page") ?? "1", 10);
  const type = searchParams.get("type"); // "production" | "preview" | "rollback" | null

  const queryString = new URLSearchParams({
    page: String(page),
    limit: "20",
    ...(type ? { type } : {}),
  }).toString();

  const { data, error, isLoading } = useSWR(
    `/api/projects/${projectId}/deployments?${queryString}`,
    fetcher,
  );

  // data shape: { data: Deployment[], total: number, page: number, limit: number }
}
```

#### Layout

```
+------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Deployments                                                        |
|                                                                    |
| Filter: [All] [Production] [Preview] [Rollback]                  |
+------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                    |
| [ready]  a1b2c3d  main     production   2h ago   34s    active   |
| [failed] e5f6g7h  main     production   5h ago   12s             |
| [ready]  i9j0k1l  main     production   1d ago   45s             |
| [ready]  m3n4o5p  main     production   2d ago   38s             |
| [ready]  q7r8s9t  main     production   3d ago   41s             |
| ...                                                               |
|                                                                    |
| < Previous  Page 1 of 3  Next >                                  |
+------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

#### Type Filter

A segmented control or button group to filter deployments by type:
- **All** -- no filter
- **Production** -- `?type=production`
- **Preview** -- `?type=preview`
- **Rollback** -- `?type=rollback`

Clicking a filter updates the URL search params (which triggers a SWR re-fetch).

#### Active Deployment Indicator

The deployment that matches the project's `productionDeploymentId` gets an "Active" badge or highlighted row to indicate it is the current production deployment.

#### Pagination Controls

Show pagination at the bottom of the list:
- "Previous" button (disabled on page 1)
- "Page X of Y" text
- "Next" button (disabled on last page)
- Clicking updates the `page` search param

### Page: `apps/dashboard/src/app/projects/[id]/deployments/[deploymentId]/page.tsx`

The deployment detail page. Shows comprehensive deployment info and build logs.

#### Data Fetching

```typescript
"use client";

import { useParams } from "next/navigation";
import useSWR from "swr";
import { fetcher } from "@/lib/swr";

export default function DeploymentDetailPage() {
  const params = useParams();
  const projectId = params.id as string;
  const deploymentId = params.deploymentId as string;

  const { data: deployment, error, isLoading } = useSWR(
    `/api/projects/${projectId}/deployments/${deploymentId}`,
    fetcher,
  );

  // Fetch build logs if available
  const { data: logs } = useSWR(
    deployment?.buildLogUrl ? deployment.buildLogUrl : null,
    (url) => fetch(url).then((res) => res.text()),
  );
}
```

