| Commit | First 7 chars, monospace, link to GitHub commit | `https://github.com/{repo}/commit/{sha}` |
| Branch | Plain text | |
| PR | `#42` (link to GitHub PR) | Only shown for preview deployments |
| Duration | Formatted duration | "34s" or "2m 15s" |
| URL | Clickable link | Opens in new tab |
| Created | Full date/time | "Feb 15, 2026 at 12:00 PM" |

### 5. `apps/dashboard/src/components/deployments/build-log-viewer.tsx`

Build log viewer with ANSI color support.

**Props:**
```typescript
interface BuildLogViewerProps {
  logs: string | null;
  isLoading: boolean;
  status: string; // deployment status
}
```

**Visual details:**
- Container: `rounded-lg bg-gray-900 p-4 overflow-auto max-h-[600px]`
- Font: `font-mono text-sm text-gray-100 leading-relaxed`
- ANSI colors rendered as inline `<span>` elements with color styles
- Auto-scroll to bottom when new content appears (during active builds)
- Loading state: "Loading build logs..." with spinner
- Empty state (queued deployment): "Build has not started yet."
- Error state: "Failed to load build logs."

**ANSI-to-HTML rendering:**

Install the `ansi-to-html` package:
```bash
pnpm add ansi-to-html --filter dashboard
```

Usage:
```typescript
import AnsiToHtml from "ansi-to-html";

const converter = new AnsiToHtml({
  fg: "#e5e7eb",      // gray-200
  bg: "#111827",      // gray-900
  newline: true,
  escapeXML: true,     // XSS prevention
  stream: false,
});

const html = converter.toHtml(logContent);
```

Render with `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`:
```typescript
<pre
  className="font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-wrap"
  dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: html }}
/>
```

**Security:** The `escapeXML: true` option in ansi-to-html ensures that any HTML in the build log output is escaped before rendering. This prevents XSS attacks from malicious build output.

### 6. `apps/dashboard/src/components/deployments/deployment-status-timeline.tsx`

A visual timeline showing the deployment status progression.

**Props:**
```typescript
interface StatusTimelineProps {
  status: string;
}
```

**Visual:**
```
[x] Queued  -->  [x] Building  -->  [x] Deploying  -->  [x] Ready
```

Each step is a circle with a connecting line. Completed steps are filled (green). The current step has a pulse animation. Failed state colors the current step red.

| Deployment Status | Timeline |
|------------------|----------|
| `queued` | Queued (active, pulsing), rest gray |
| `building` | Queued (done), Building (active), rest gray |
| `deploying` | Queued (done), Building (done), Deploying (active), rest gray |
| `ready` | All green/done |
| `failed` | Last reached step is red |
| `archived` | All gray |

